There really should be a state "iodine board" that tracks the iodine levels and hypothyroidism prevalence of the population in various counties and cities and then sets the iodination level of salt to optimize thyroid function year by year. Maybe they can also selenize the salt.

Like a lot of 20th century Faucian health ideas iodinating salt was a pretty genius move, but you can't just infinitely keep dumping iodine into the food supply, there is an optimal amount that obviously varies between places and too much also does harm. You have to be smarter...

My ultimate deep contrarian belief is that using the greentext arrows outside of 4chan is actually ok and the practice of using the "greater than" sign to quote someone or yourself is actually older than imageboards and goes back to very early internet forums and emails

There was a time when the text didn't turn green. Admittedly before my day, but I still know about it. The text actually turning green was a brief anomaly in the timeline of the internet. I believe we should let people greentext on twitter and whatever website comes in the future
